race.comment: MASTER OF DISGUISE (11) was scratched from Canterbury on Wednesday to be kept for this. Led and tried hard but found one better last time out over 1175m at Albury. Yet to prove herself beyond six furlongs but with the light weight from a good draw she gets her chance. ROUGE MOULIN (6) is knocking on the door, the latest offering a closing second over 1200m at Warren. Has raced once over this distance at got the cash. Very fit and after the claim is very nicely placed. LIFE'S A PARTY (10) has a similar profile to ROUGE MOULIN with some recent minor placings over shorter journeys. Will put herself in the race and should be in the finish. Distance specialist SCOPICS (15) caught the eye at Kembla last start and is a chance down in the weights. TAVOLO (7) has been racing well over longer trips. Query coming back to 1300m at this stage of the prep but she is too honest to rule out.
